column1:
If there are cyan/light blue blocks available, replace the existing blue blocks with them;
Then to the left of the leftmost top purple block, place a cyan/light blue block;
Do the same as the previous step on the other side.

Place a green block on top of the existing one;
Place another green block to the left of that one;
Break the first block you placed.

Place two green blocks to the left of the topmost green block;
Place two green blocks under the last block you placed;
Break the leftmost green block on the top row.

Facing North, move to the left edge of the grid and place a red block;
Place a red block on top of it;
Place a red block on each side of the bottom one.

Facing North, move to the right edge of the grid and place a purple block;
Place a purple block on top of it;
Place a purple block on each side of the bottom one.

Place a purple block on top of the topmost one;
Place a purple block to the left of that;
Remove the first block you placed.

Place a purple block below the lowest purple block (not counting the tower itself);
Place a purple block to the left of that;
Remove the first block you placed.

Place a blue block on top of the orange tower;
Place a block to the left and right of the blue block;
Break the middle blue block.

Place a blue block to the right of the rightmost blue block;
Place two blue blocks on top of that block;
Break the first block you placed.
